          <div property="content:encoded" class="field-item even"><p>Every so often, advocates and vendors of proprietary/closed source software attempt a FUD (Fear, Uncertainty &amp; Doubt) campaign of comment and link-baiting in order to reframe the conversation around Open Source. The arguments brought up in these discussions are predictable and generally straw man arguments that hold little water, so I wanted to take time to break these down and show the real value proposition of Open Source platforms, web content management systems generally, and Drupal specifically.</p></div>
